                    <span>I felt I should balance out the 2 star rating left by Dean Hiller, who really liked the book but gave it 2 stars because, to paraphrase in his own words, "he is anal".  People look seriously at reviews, and the number of stars given is important. I see 4 or less, I probabably don't buy the book.  If you don't want to help people in their decision making, then keep your mouth shut.  You should rate book with respect to alternatives, not according to your own bizarre personal psychology.</span>
                  
              
